**Tracing the Missing Blue**

I'm puzzled, the accent blue seems to have vanished, despite the previous edits. I remember implementing the pixel-perfect adjustments and removing the card styling for "My Projects & R&D" as requested, specifically in `ResumePaper.tsx` and `App.tsx`. Perhaps the changes introduced an unintended side effect? I will revisit the code to troubleshoot the loss of the accent color.


**Pinpointing the Color Shift**

I've been examining the color implementation within `ProjectBlock` and `ExperienceBlock`, specifically their integration within `ResumePaper.tsx`. I noticed that `index.html` defines `#0057FF` as `resume-accent`. Comparing the old and new `ProjectBlock` versions, I found subtle changes. The role now utilizes `text-resume-accent` for the new `ProjectBlock`, which should have the blue color that is missing, but something must be overriding it, as well as several other elements throughout the resume.


**Identifying Color Anomalies**

I've traced the color shift to `ExperienceBlock`, specifically the company name, now `text-resume-secondary` instead of the original `text-resume-accent`. Also, the "View" link/icon in `ProjectBlock` changed from `text-resume-accent` to `text-resume-muted`, with blue only on hover. However, the `ResumeHeader` links still use `text-resume-accent`. The skills bullets in the new `ResumePaper.tsx` remain blue. My focus now is on understanding the design rationale behind these deliberate color changes.


**Restoring the Accent**

My immediate plan is to reinstate the blue accent in `ResumePaper.tsx`. I'll revert the `ExperienceBlock`'s company name to `text-resume-accent` and the `ProjectBlock`'s "View" link to the same. While I'm at it, I'll confirm that the `highlightText` function continues to render numbers in `text-resume-primary`, which was black bold in the initial setup. I want to address the loss of visual impact from the company name and project links. The resume header links are unaffected.


**Revisiting Accent Placement**

I've been re-examining the code in `ResumePaper.tsx` more closely, specifically the `ExperienceBlock` and `ProjectBlock` components, and will modify them. The company name in `ExperienceBlock` was changed to `text-resume-secondary`, so I will return this to `text-resume-accent`, as it was originally. The "View" link in `ProjectBlock` will also get its accent color back. I also verified the color of the `SectionHeader` and confirmed it's appropriate. Finally, I will ensure that the `item.role` still uses `text-resume-accent` for the new `ProjectBlock`.


**Reinstating Blue Elements**

I've restored the blue accent to the "View" link in `ProjectBlock` and reinstated the blue company name within `ExperienceBlock`. I am also continuing to use `text-resume-accent` for icons and links in `ResumeHeader`. I left `highlightText` with `text-resume-primary` because that was consistent with the original setup. I applied the following changes to `components/ResumePaper.tsx`:
```typescript
// ExperienceBlock
<span className="font-semibold text-resume-accent">{item.company}</span>

// ProjectBlock
<a href={item.link} ... className="... text-resume-accent ...">
```
I confirmed that the "переделай My Projects & R&D оно недолжно быть в карточька" request was also successfully implemented.


**Verifying Previous Changes**

I'm now cross-referencing my recent modifications to ensure color consistency, mainly within `ResumePaper.tsx`. I confirm I correctly addressed the company name and "View" link elements from the previous turn, and that I retained them as `text-resume-accent`. I am now focusing on any further color-related discrepancies introduced during this process. I'll meticulously compare and contrast elements that have changed since the start, ensuring the integrity of the blue accent.


**Restoring the Link Accent**

I've decided to reinstate the direct use of the blue accent color to the project links. Previously, it had a muted appearance on its own, only changing to blue on hover. I've re-applied the `text-resume-accent` class directly, which ensures the links have the primary blue color. I've also verified the bullet point fix, that uses a robust `flex` container with a `shrink-0` setting. I've ensured that the contact icons in `ResumeHeader` still use the accent class as well.


**Providing the ResumePaper.tsx**

I am now ready to present the full content of `components/ResumePaper.tsx` with all the necessary color corrections implemented. The changes ensure a consistent and visually impactful use of the blue accent, primarily focusing on `ExperienceBlock`'s company name, `ProjectBlock`'s "View" link, the `ResumeHeader`, and the bullet point fix, while ensuring `highlightText` retains its original setup. All these aspects should now maintain their intended color.

```typescript
import React from 'react';
import { ICONS } from '../constants';
import { ExperienceItem, ProjectItem, ResumeData } from '../types';
import { PlayCircle } from 'lucide-react';

interface ResumePaperProps {
  data: ResumeData;
}

// Helper to bold specific patterns
const highlightText = (text: string) => {
  const regex = /(\d+(?:[.,]\d+)?(?:%|x)|\$[0-9.]+[MK]?\+?)/g;
  const parts = text.split(regex);
  return parts.map((part, i) => 
    regex.test(part) ? <strong key={i} className="font-bold text-resume-primary">{part}</strong> : part
  );
};

const SectionHeader: React.FC<{ title: string; className?: string }> = ({ title, className = "mt-8" }) => (
  <div className={`flex items-center gap-3 mb-6 break-after-avoid ${className}`}>
