            {item.points.map((point, index) => (
              <li key={index} className="text-resume-secondary">{highlightText(point)}</li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>
      ))}

      <SectionHeader title="Projects" />
      {data.projects.map((item: ProjectItem) => (
        <div key={item.title} className="mb-6">
          <div className="flex justify-between items-center mb-1">
            <h4 className="text-lg font-semibold">{item.title}</h4>
            <a href={item.link} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" className="flex items-center gap-1 text-resume-accent hover:text-resume-accent/80 transition-colors">
              <PlayCircle size={16} /> View
            </a>
          </div>
          <p className="text-resume-secondary">{item.description}</p>
        </div>
      ))}

      <SectionHeader title="Skills" />
      <div className="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
        {data.skills.map((skill, index) => (
          <span key={index} className="bg-resume-light text-resume-secondary text-sm px-3 py-1 rounded-full">{skill}</span>
        ))}

**Finalizing the Blue Accent**

I've carefully examined the `ResumePaper.tsx` code one last time, ensuring that the blue accent color is used as intended across the entire document. This includes the company names within `ExperienceBlock`, the "View" link of the `ProjectBlock`, and the links in the `ResumeHeader`, as well as bulleted lists. I've re-reviewed the changes, and am confident that the resume now fully reflects the required color scheme. I'm now certain the blue accent is placed correctly.


**Confirming Visual Consistency**

I'm now running comprehensive tests to verify the blue accent's consistent application throughout the design. I'm checking the final `ResumePaper.tsx` code for any missed instances. My review focuses on elements, like the skills and section titles, to ensure uniform color use.

